  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\nWith the finalization of [RIP-7212](https://github.com/ethereum/RIPs/blob/master/RIPS/rip-7212.md) and the progress of [EIP-7212](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-7212), more forge users will want a way to test signing using the secp256r1 curve. \r\n\r\nI propose a new cheat code\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction signP256(uint256 privateKey, bytes32 digest) external returns (bytes32 r, bytes32 s);\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n[P256](https://csrc.nist.gov/csrc/media/events/workshop-on-elliptic-curve-cryptography-standards/documents/papers/session6-adalier-mehmet.pdf) is the general abbreviation for this signing curve, though maybe a more verbose name would be more clear, given Ethereum uses secp256k1. Open to ideas.  ",
